status = 'pending'\n- `idx_event_queue_status`: ON (status, created_at)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Redaction Policy (peek/src/server/audit/redact.ts)\n\n**Full Content:**\n\nThe redaction module exports the following functions:\n\n- **`looksLikeSecret(value: string): boolean`** — Tests value against five regex patterns (JWT_PATTERN, DB_URL_PATTERN, PRIVATE_KEY_PATTERN, BEARER_PATTERN, CF_ACCESS_HEADER_PATTERN). Returns true if any pattern matches.\n\n- **`redactScalar(value: PeekAuditScalar): PeekAuditScalar`** — If value is a string and `looksLikeSecret` returns true, replaces with `PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED`; otherwise returns unchanged.\n\n- **`redactNullableString(value: string | null): string | null`** — Handles nullable strings: passes null through, otherwise applies `looksLikeSecret` test and redacts if matched.\n\n- **`redactChange(change: PeekAuditChange): PeekAuditChange`** — Applies `redactScalar` to both `before` and `after` fields while preserving the `field` name.\n\n- **`redactPayload(payload: PeekAuditPayload): PeekAuditPayload`** — The main entry point. Redacts `route`, `actionId`, `resourceType`, `resourceId`, `filterSummary`, `requestId`, and `rejectionReason` as nullable strings; redacts each `change` in the changes array; passes through `actorEmail`, `resultCount` unchanged.\n\n**Key Types Used:**\n- `PeekAuditChange` = { field: string; before: PeekAuditScalar; after: PeekAuditScalar }\n- `PeekAuditPayload` = { actorEmail: string; route: string | null; actionId: string | null; resourceType: string | null; resourceId: string | null; filterSummary: string | null; resultCount: number | null; requestId: string | null; rejectionReason: string | null; changes: ReadonlyArray<PeekAuditChange> | null }\n- `PeekAuditScalar` = string | number | boolean | null\n- `PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED` = \"[REDACTED]\"\n\n---\n\n### 3. FR-4 View-Model Conventions (peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts)\n\n**PeekMetric Structure:**\n```ts\nexport type PeekMetric = {\n  id: string;\n  label: string;\n  value: number | string | null;\n  valueDisplay: string;\n  unit: string | null;\n  source: string;\n  windowLabel: string;\n  asOf: string | null;\n  definition: string;\n  freshness: PeekMetricFreshness;\n  drilldownHref: string | null;\n};\n\nexport type PeekMetricFreshness = \"live\" | \"cached\" | \"manual\" | \"sampled\";\n```\n\n**List-Result Envelope Types:**\n```ts\nexport type PeekPagination = {\n  page: number;\n  pageSize: number;\n  totalCount: number;\n  totalPages: number;\n};\n\nexport type PeekTableViewModel<TRow extends PeekTableRowBase> = {\n  columns: ReadonlyArray<PeekTableColumn>;\n  rows: ReadonlyArray<TRow>;\n  pagination: PeekPagination;\n  filters: ReadonlyArray<PeekTableFilter>;\n  sort: PeekTableSort | null;\n  empty: PeekEmptyState;\n};\n```\n\n**PEEK_* Constants Already Declared:**\n- `PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED = \"[REDACTED]\"`\n- `PEEK_AUDIT_EVENT_TYPES: ReadonlyArray<PeekAuditEventType>` = [\"peek.search\", \"peek.user.view_sensitive\", \"peek.export\", \"peek.access.denied\", \"peek.change.applied\", \"peek.change.rejected\"]\n- `PEEK_SEARCH_DEFAULT_PER_GROUP_LIMIT = 5`\n- `PEEK_SEARCH_MAX_PER_GROUP_LIMIT = 25`\n- `PEEK_EXPORT_ROW_CAP_DEFAULT = 5000`\n- `PEEK_GAME_IDS: ReadonlyArray<PeekGameId>` = [\"flipyou\", \"potshot\", \"closecall\"]\n- `PEEK_GROWTH_OVERVIEW_METRIC_IDS: ReadonlyArray<PeekGrowthOverviewMetricId>` (8 ids)\n- `PEEK_GAME_OVERVIEW_METRIC_IDS: ReadonlyArray<PeekGameOverviewMetricId>` (6 ids)\n- `PEEK_ROUND_PHASES: ReadonlyArray<PeekRoundPhase>` = [\"created\", \"locked\", \"settling\", \"settled\", \"expired\"]\n- `PEEK_ROUNDS_GAME_IDS: ReadonlyArray<PeekRoundsGameId>` = [\"flipyou\", \"potshot\"]\n- `PEEK_CLOSECALL_PHASES: ReadonlyArray<PeekCloseCallPhase>` = [\"open\", \"settled\", \"refunded\"]\n- `PEEK_CLOSECALL_OUTCOMES: ReadonlyArray<PeekCloseCallOutcome>` = [\"pending\", \"green\", \"red\", \"refund\"]\n- `PEEK_REWARDS_OVERVIEW_METRIC_IDS: ReadonlyArray<PeekRewardsOverviewMetricId>` (4 ids)\n- `PEEK_DOGPILE_STATUSES: ReadonlyArray<PeekDogpileStatus>` = [\"scheduled\", \"active\", \"ended\", \"cancelled\"]\n- `PEEK_DOGPILE_FRAUD_OVERVIEW_METRIC_IDS: ReadonlyArray<PeekDogpileFraudOverviewMetricId>` (5 ids)\n- `PEEK_CHALLENGES_OVERVIEW_METRIC_IDS: ReadonlyArray<PeekChallengesOverviewMetricId>` (5 ids)\n\n**Existing Queue-Related Types:**\n- `PeekUserQueueEventRow` (lines 149-158) — used in per-user detail view; fields: id, eventType, status, attempts, maxAttempts, scheduledAt, createdAt, error\n- `PeekUserAttentionFlags` (lines 160-166) — includes `deadQueueEvent: boolean` flag\n\n**No PEEK_QUEUE_* constants or PeekQueueEvent* types are pre-declared**, so your new queue-overview layer is free to introduce:\n- `PEEK_QUEUE_EVENTS_DEFAULT_LIMIT`, `PEEK_QUEUE_EVENTS_MAX_LIMIT`\n- `PeekQueueEventRow` (for list view), `PeekQueueEventListResult`, `PeekQueueEventFilters`, etc.\n- Optional metric constants like `PEEK_QUEUE_OVERVIEW_METRIC_IDS` if you plan a metrics strip\n\n---\n\n### 4. Representative Query Module: get-dogpile-and-fraud.ts\n\n**Structure & Patterns:**\n\n```ts\n// Imports\nimport type { Sql } from \"postgres\";\nimport {\n  type PeekDogpileEventFilters,\n  type PeekDogpileEventRow,\n  type PeekDogpileFraudOverview,\n  type PeekDogpileFraudOverviewMetricId,\n  type PeekFraudFlagFilters,\n  type PeekFraudFlagListRow,\n  type PeekMetric,\n} from \"../../../lib/types/peek\";\nimport { getSqlClient } from \"../client\";\n\n// Export default/max limits (constants)\nexport const PEEK_DOGPILE_EVENTS_DEFAULT_LIMIT = 100;\nexport const PEEK_DOGPILE_EVENTS_MAX_LIMIT = 500;\nexport const PEEK_FRAUD_FLAGS_DEFAULT_LIMIT = 100;\nexport const PEEK_FRAUD_FLAGS_MAX_LIMIT = 500;\nexport const PEEK_DOGPILE_FRAUD_OVERVIEW_WINDOW_HOURS = 24;\n\n// Export option interfaces (discriminate queries via function signature)\nexport type ListDogpileEventsOptions = {\n  sql?: Sql;\n  limit?: number;\n  filters?: Partial<PeekDogpileEventFilters>;\n};\n\n// Helper functions (shared across query functions)\nfunction clampLimit(raw: number | undefined, fallback: number, max: number): number {\n  if (typeof raw !== \"number\" || !Number.isFinite(raw)) return fallback;\n  const floored = Math.floor(raw);\n  if (floored <= 0) return 1;\n  return Math.min(max, floored);\n}\n\nfunction trimOrNull(value: string | null | undefined): string | null {\n  if (typeof value !== \"string\") return null;\n  const trimmed = value.trim();\n  return trimmed.length > 0 ? trimmed : null;\n}\n\nfunction readInt(value: number | string | null | undefined): number {\n  if (typeof value === \"number\" && Number.isFinite(value)) return value;\n  if (typeof value === \"string\") {\n    const parsed = Number.parseInt(value, 10);\n    return Number.isFinite(parsed) ? parsed : 0;\n  }\n  return 0;\n}\n\nfunction formatCount(count: number): string {\n  return count.toLocaleString(\"en-US\");\n}\n\n// Main list query (bounded, filtered, pagination implicit in limit)\nexport async function listDogpileEvents(\n  options: ListDogpileEventsOptions = {},\n): Promise<ReadonlyArray<PeekDogpileEventRow>> {\n  const sql = options.sql ?? (getSqlClient() as unknown as Sql);\n  const limit = clampLimit(\n    options.limit,\n    PEEK_DOGPILE_EVENTS_DEFAULT_LIMIT,\n    PEEK_DOGPILE_EVENTS_MAX_LIMIT,\n  );\n\n  const filters = options.filters ?? {};\n  const status = trimOrNull(filters.status ?? null);\n  const startsFrom = trimOrNull(filters.startsFrom ?? null);\n  const startsTo = trimOrNull(filters.startsTo ?? null);\n\n  const rows = await sql<Array<{ ... }>>`\n    select ...\n    from dogpile_events d\n    left join campaigns c on c.id = d.campaign_id\n    where\n      (${status === null} or d.status = ${status ?? \"\"})\n      and (${startsFrom === null} or d.starts_at >= ${startsFrom ?? \"\"}::timestamptz)\n      and (${startsTo === null} or d.starts_at < ${startsTo ?? \"\"}::timestamptz)\n    order by d.starts_at desc, d.id desc\n    limit ${limit}\n  `;\n\n  return rows.map((row) => ({ ... }));\n}\n\n// Metric blueprint + builder (if overview metrics needed)\ntype MetricBlueprint = {\n  id: PeekDogpileFraudOverviewMetricId;\n  label: string;\n  unit: string | null;\n  source: string;\n  windowLabel: string;\n  definition: string;\n  drilldownHref: string | null;\n};\n\nfunction buildMetric(\n  blueprint: MetricBlueprint,\n  raw: number,\n  display: string,\n  asOf: string,\n): PeekMetric {\n  return {\n    id: blueprint.id,\n    label: blueprint.label,\n    value: raw,\n    valueDisplay: display,\n    unit: blueprint.unit,\n    source: blueprint.source,\n    windowLabel: blueprint.windowLabel,\n    asOf,\n    definition: blueprint.definition,\n    freshness: \"live\",\n    drilldownHref: blueprint.drilldownHref,\n  };\n}\n\n// Parallelized overview query (Promise.all for all counts)\nexport async function getDogpileFraudOverview(\n  options: DogpileFraudOverviewOptions = {},\n): Promise<PeekDogpileFraudOverview> {\n  const sql = options.sql ?? (getSqlClient() as unknown as Sql);\n  const now = options.now ?? new Date();\n  const generatedAt = now.toISOString();\n  const windowHours = clampLimit(\n    options.windowHours,\n    PEEK_DOGPILE_FRAUD_OVERVIEW_WINDOW_HOURS,\n    24 * 30,\n  );\n  const since = new Date(now.getTime() - windowHours * 60 * 60 * 1000);\n  const sinceIso = since.toISOString();\n\n  const [\n    scheduledRows,\n    activeRows,\n    endedWindowRows,\n    cancelledWindowRows,\n    openFraudRows,\n  ] = await Promise.all([\n    sql<Array<{ value: number | string }>>`...`,\n    sql<Array<{ value: number | string }>>`...`,\n    sql<Array<{ value: number | string }>>`...`,\n    sql<Array<{ value: number | string }>>`...`,\n    sql<Array<{ value: number | string }>>`...`,\n  ]);\n\n  const scheduled = readInt(scheduledRows[0]?.value ?? 0);\n  // ... extract other counts ...\n\n  const blueprints: ReadonlyArray<{ blueprint: MetricBlueprint; raw: number; display: string }> = [\n    { blueprint: { id: \"dogpile.scheduled\", ... }, raw: scheduled, display: formatCount(scheduled) },\n    // ... more blueprints ...\n  ];\n\n  return {\n    generatedAt,\n    metrics: blueprints.map(({ blueprint, raw, display }) =>\n      buildMetric(blueprint, raw, display, generatedAt),\n    ),\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key Patterns Observed:**\n1. **Imports**: Type imports first (peek.ts types), then `postgres` Sql type, then `getSqlClient` helper\n2. **Constants**: PEEK_*_DEFAULT_LIMIT, PEEK_*_MAX_LIMIT, and window/threshold constants\n3. **Option Types**: Explicit discriminated interfaces for each query function; include `sql?: Sql` for testing, `limit?: number`, `filters?: Partial<FilterType>`\n4. **Helper Functions**: `clampLimit`, `trimOrNull`, `readInt`/`readSum`, `formatCount`/`formatLamports`\n5. **SQL Binding**: postgres tagged-template with explicit type annotations for row shape; conditional predicates use `${filterNull === null} or column = ${value}` pattern\n6. **Mapping**: `.map()` to shape rows into exported types; bigints cast to `::text`, timestamps cast to `::text`\n7. **Overview Queries**: Run count queries in parallel via `Promise.all`, extract via `readInt`, build metrics from blueprints\n8. **Metric Structure**: MetricBlueprint (id, label, unit, source, windowLabel, definition, drilldownHref), buildMetric helper, return type = Overview envelope with generatedAt + metrics array\n\n---\n\n### 5. Test Helper Conventions (get-dogpile-and-fraud.test.ts - Excerpt)\n\n**Test Setup & SQL Mock Pattern:**\n\n```ts\nimport { describe, expect, it } from \"vitest\";\nimport type { Sql } from \"postgres\";\nimport {\n  PEEK_DOGPILE_EVENTS_DEFAULT_LIMIT,\n  PEEK_DOGPILE_EVENTS_MAX_LIMIT,\n  getDogpileEventsFraudOverview,\n  listDogpileEvents,\n  // ...\n} from \"../get-dogpile-and-fraud\";\nimport {\n  PEEK_DOGPILE_FRAUD_OVERVIEW_METRIC_IDS,\n  PEEK_DOGPILE_STATUSES,\n  type PeekDogpileFraudOverviewMetricId,\n} from \"../../../../lib/types/peek\";\n\n// --- SQL Mock Factory ---\n\ntype SqlCall = {\n  text: string;\n  values: ReadonlyArray<unknown>;\n};\n\ntype ResponseValue = ReadonlyArray<Record<string, unknown>> | Error;\n\ntype SqlMock = {\n  sql: Sql;\n  calls: ReadonlyArray<SqlCall>;\n};\n\nfunction createSqlMock(responses: ReadonlyArray<ResponseValue>): SqlMock {\n  const calls: SqlCall[] = [];\n  let cursor = 0;\n\n  const fn = (strings: TemplateStringsArray, ...values: unknown[]) => {\n    const text = [...strings].join(\"?\");\n    calls.push({ text, values: [...values] });\n    const next = responses[cursor++];\n    if (next instanceof Error) return Promise.reject(next);\n    return Promise.resolve(next ?? []);\n  };\n\n  const sql = fn as unknown as Sql;\n  return { sql, calls };\n}\n\n// --- Read-Only Guarantee Helper ---\n\nfunction expectReadOnly(call: SqlCall) {\n  // Read-only guarantee: every dogpile + fraud query must be SELECT only.\n  // FR-14 keeps every dogpile_events or fraud_flags write behind a mutation\n  // action id, none of which are implemented yet.\n  expect(call.text).not.toMatch(/\\binsert\\s+into\\b/i);\n  expect(call.text).not.toMatch(/\\bupdate\\s+\\w/i);\n  expect(call.text).not.toMatch(/\\bdelete\\s+from\\b/i);\n  expect(call.text).toMatch(/\\bselect\\b/i);\n}\n\n// --- Test Suite ---\n\ndescribe(\"listDogpileEvents\", () => {\n  it(\"default limit: clamps to PEEK_DOGPILE_EVENTS_DEFAULT_LIMIT and reads from dogpile_events with the campaigns left join\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock([[]]);\n    await listDogpileEvents({ sql: mock.sql });\n\n    expect(mock.calls).toHaveLength(1);\n    const call = mock.calls[0];\n    expectReadOnly(call);\n    expect(call.text).toMatch(/from dogpile_events d/i);\n    expect(call.text).toMatch(/left join campaigns c on c\\.id = d\\.campaign_id/i);\n    expect(call.values).toContain(PEEK_DOGPILE_EVENTS_DEFAULT_LIMIT);\n  });\n\n  it(\"limit clamps to MAX when caller asks for more\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock([[]]);\n    await listDogpileEvents({\n      sql: mock.sql,\n      limit: PEEK_DOGPILE_EVENTS_MAX_LIMIT + 100,\n    });\n    expect(mock.calls[0].values).toContain(PEEK_DOGPILE_EVENTS_MAX_LIMIT);\n  });\n\n  // More tests...\n});\n```\n\n**Key Testing Patterns:**\n1. **createSqlMock**: Tagged-template stub that dequeues responses per call; joins template strings with \"?\"; records { text, values } pair\n2. **expectReadOnly**: Enforces SELECT-only (no INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE); documents read-only guarantee\n3. **Test assertions**: Check SQL text matches regex patterns, values contain expected limit/filter, call count matches expected parallelism\n4. **Response mocking**: Pass array of response arrays (or Error) to mock multiple queries in order; tests verify order of execution via call indices\n\n---\n\n### 6. Command-Center Attention Query (get-command-center-attention.ts — Dead Events Section)\n\n**Relevant Excerpt (lines 125-129):**\n\n```ts\nsql<AttentionRow[]>`\n  select count(*)::int as \"value\"\n  from event_queue\n  where status = 'dead'\n`,\n```\n\n**Context in Overview:**\nThe command-center attention query runs 7 queries in parallel via Promise.all:\n1. Failed referral claims (status IN 'failed', 'error')\n2. **Dead queue events (status = 'dead')** ← your reference\n3. Stuck rounds (FlipYou/Pot Shot)\n4. Stuck Close Call rounds\n5. Pending SOL crate payouts\n6. Stale active Dogpile events\n7. High-value exports\n\nEach query returns a single integer count. The dead queue events query:\n- **Table**: event_queue\n- **Filter**: WHERE status = 'dead'\n- **Metric ID**: \"dead_queue_events\"\n- **Label**: \"Dead queue events\"\n- **Unit**: \"events\"\n- **Definition**: \"Event-queue rows in 'dead' status — past max attempts and not retried.\"\n- **Drilldown**: \"/operations/queue?status=dead\"\n- **Window**: \"All time\" (no time-window filter)\n\nYour queue-overview query should use the same status values and join semantics.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Source Files Listing\n\n**Query Modules** (`peek/src/server/db/queries/*.ts`):\n- count-peek-users.ts\n- get-challenges.ts\n- get-command-center-attention.ts\n- get-dogpile-and-fraud.ts\n- get-game-rounds.ts\n- get-games-overview.ts\n- get-growth-referrals.ts\n- get-peek-summary.ts\n- get-peek-user-detail.ts\n- get-points-and-crates.ts\n- get-recent-operator-events.ts\n- get-rewards.ts\n- get-round-detail.ts\n- list-peek-users.ts\n- universal-search.ts\n\n**Audit Modules** (`peek/src/server/audit/*.ts`):\n- index.ts\n- redact.ts\n- writer.ts\n- __tests__/writer.test.ts (test only)\n\n**Type Definitions** (`peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts`):\n- **EXISTS** ✓ (confirmed)\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nYou now have:\n1. **Full event_queue schema** with all columns, types, defaults, constraints, and indexes\n2. **Redaction API** — five functions (looksLikeSecret, redactScalar, redactNullableString, redactChange, redactPayload) with clear patterns\n3. **FR-4 conventions** — PeekMetric shape, PeekTableViewModel envelope, pagination primitives, and 10+ existing PEEK_* constant patterns\n4. **Query structure template** from dogpile-and-fraud.ts — imports, constants, option types, helpers (clampLimit, trimOrNull, readInt, formatCount), bounded list queries with conditional predicates, parallel-loaded overview metrics\n5. **Test helper conventions** — createSqlMock factory, expectReadOnly guarantor, test patterns for limits/filters/order\n6. **Command-center reference** — exact dead-events count query (status = 'dead' on event_queue) so your overview is consistent\n7. **All file paths** — 15 query modules, 3 audit modules, types file confirmed\n\nReady to build your Event Queue admin layer!"}],"totalDurationMs":100030,"totalTokens":85632,"totalToolUseCount":31,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2233,"cache_read_input_tokens":77122,"output_tokens":6271,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2233},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_token